-- Goldman, TPG Set to Buy Candover's Ontex for $1.5 Billion, Telegraph Says
-- Grant Smith
-- 2010-07-04T06:12:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-04/goldman-tpg-set-to-buy-candover-s-ontex-for-1-5-billion-telegraph-says.html

          
          
             The private equity wing of Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. and TPG Capital are to buy diaper maker Ontex
from Candover Investments Plc for 1.2 billion euros ($1.5
billion), the  Sunday Telegraph  reported, without saying where it
got the information.  
 The deal, which faltered when Goldmanâ€™s initial private
equity partner withdrew, may be announced as early as this week,
according to the newspaper. Ontex has about 60 percent of the
European market for non-label diapers, the Telegraph said.  
 Goldman Sachs spokeswoman Fiona Laffan declined to comment
on the report.  
